subSubSection.paragraph:
Discussion:
The grouping of mylagaulids with aplodontines is one of the strongest associations found in phylogenetic analyses of aplodontids (
Hopkins, 2001a
; 
Hopkins, 2001b
; 
Hopkins, 2003
). This taxon is composed of all the fully hypsodont (having cheek tooth crown height greater than crown length) aplodontids, as well as the mesodont aplodontine precursor 

R. mcgrewi

.
